# Single Source of Truth for Cross-Surface Constants

## The mistake this prevents

Changing the app PIN from 6 to 4 digits required edits in **three**
files (`pin_setup_screen.dart`, `pin_lock_screen.dart`,
`change_pin_sheet.dart`) — each redeclared its own `_pinLength = 6`,
its own `LengthLimitingTextInputFormatter(6)`, and its own "6-digit
PIN" copy. Forgetting any one of them yields a silent, asymmetric
UX where setup accepts 4 digits but Change-PIN demands 6.

## Root cause

A configuration value (PIN length, max attempts, lockout window,
currency precision, file size cap, …) was treated as a **screen-local
literal** instead of as a domain tunable. Once it appears on more
than one surface, the literal becomes a duplication smell.

## Mandatory recipe

When a value satisfies **any** of these, hoist it into a single
`abstract final class` constant in the feature's `domain/` folder
(or `core/constants/` if the value is app-wide):

- It is the same value in two or more files.
- A user-facing string contains it (e.g. "4-digit PIN").
- Validators / input formatters / hashers all need it.
- Changing it is a product decision, not a screen-local choice.

```dart
abstract final class AuthConfig {
  static const int pinLength = 4;
  static String get pinLengthLabel => '$pinLength-digit';
}
```

Every screen, validator, formatter, and copy string MUST read from
this constant. **No more `static const _pinLength = 4;` per screen.**

## Anti-patterns

- `static const _xxxLength = N;` redeclared in each screen / sheet.
- `LengthLimitingTextInputFormatter(6)` with the literal `6` next to
  the matching validator `v.length != 6` and hint `"6-digit PIN"` —
  three places to forget.
- Hard-coding the value in tests too. Tests SHOULD use the constant
  for length-dependent assertions (but plaintext fixture PINs like
  `'1234'` are fine — they just need to be the right length).

## Regression test pattern

Before declaring a change complete, grep for the **old literal** and
the **string form** of it across the repo:

```bash
rg --no-heading -n '\b6\b' lib/ test/ | rg -i 'pin|digit'
```

If anything outside the central constant matches, it's a duplication
that will rot.

## Stack-specific note (Flutter)

- Place the constant in `lib/features/<feature>/domain/<feature>_config.dart`
  for feature-scoped values.
- Place it in `lib/core/constants/` for app-wide values.
- Use `abstract final class` so the type can never be instantiated or
  extended — this is the modern Dart 3 idiom for static-only holders.
